
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-l3vpn-end-system-requirements-00.txt'>
    <title>"Requirements for Extending BGP/MPLS VPNs to End-Systems", Maria Napierala, Luyuan Fang</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-ietf-l3vpn-end-system-requirements-00.txt</link>
    <description>The proven scalability and extensibility of the BGP/MPLS IP VPNs (IP VPN) technology has made it an attractive candidate for data center/cloud virtualization. Virtualized end-system environment imposes additional requirements to MPLS/BGP VPN technology. This document provides the requirements for extending IP VPN technology (in original or modified versions) into the end-systems/hosts, such as a server in a data center.</description>
    <dc:date>2014-10-02T07:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
